abstract.value: The Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Printed Ephemera Collection on the Communications Workers of America is an artificial collection, collected and assembled by the Tamiment Library over the course of several decades. The collection consists of contracts, agreements, constitutions, convention proceedings, and reports, as well as printed ephemera such as fliers, circular letters, newspapers clippings, pamphlets and publications ranging in date from 1941-2008. A substantial portion of the material comes from the national body of the CWA and its various departments, however there is also material in the collection from districts and locals from around the country, but largely from locals in and around the New York area.
